37:08.241 --> 37:18.571
that even the youngest children in a county like 
this, an isolated community, know that sort of

37:08.241 --> 37:18.571
thing. Is that right? You mighty well believe. And 
we knew to ride. We knew how to ride.

37:27.224 --> 37:38.764
Why, I can remember that grandfather gave me, and 
my saddle was made, it had a great big horn, what we

37:27.224 --> 37:38.764
called a Mexican saddle horn. He told me, he said, 
if you have to grab a hold of something, sister, you

37:41.409 --> 37:48.962
can't hold on to that horn. Grab that string on the 
side. I know what string you mean, right? So I never

37:56.158 --> 37:59.402
was taught to hold on to a saddle. That wasn't my cup 
of tea. Right. From little. I have a pair of spurs

38:05.190 --> 38:10.877
that my grandmother gave me, engraved Eliza on. 
She has, and I gave them to the park thinking they'd

38:11.699 --> 38:17.426
appreciate them and they'd put them up, and 
they've never been put out. So I don't know where

38:17.526 --> 38:19.489
they are. They're a lot. They're cataloged to 
uselessness. I guess they are cataloged to

38:24.320 --> 38:27.004
uselessness. Right. I didn't have a 
granddaughter. I mean, at that time, I mean, well,

38:29.727 --> 38:35.374
Debbie, I could have given them to her. I have one. I 
gave her. I have one left. I couldn't find it, but.

38:42.993 --> 38:48.764
In moving, never having moved in 58 years, in 
